File:Â The CRL Rights Commission will from Monday hold hearings on reports of human rights abuses at KwaSizabantu. JOHANNESBURG - Reports of human rights abuses at KwaSizabantu will receive an airing on Monday. The CRL Rights Commission will be conducting hearings on the affair. The commission will meet with alleged victims and leaders of the Christian mission. According to News24, reports of abuse go all the way back to the 1980s. The mission owns the aQuelle bottled water brand. It also supplies fruit and vegetables to some of South Africa's biggest retailers.